---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Delete Your Fierro Account"
  description="How to permanently delete your Fierro account and all associated data."
>
  <!-- Lightweight dark header band -->
  <section class="bg-gunmetal pt-28 pb-10">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-off-white">Delete Your Fierro Account</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-off-white/60">Account and data deletion</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Prose content -->
  <section class="bg-off-white py-12 lg:py-16">
    <article class="prose-legal mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p>
        If you would like to delete your Fierro account and all associated data, you can
        do so directly from the app. Follow the steps below.
      </p>

      <h2>How to Delete Your Account</h2>
      <p>
        To delete your Fierro account and all associated data, open the Fierro app, go to
        <strong>Settings</strong>, and tap <strong>"Delete Account"</strong>. You will be
        asked to confirm your decision before the deletion is processed.
      </p>

      <h2>What Data Is Deleted</h2>
      <p>
        When you delete your account, the following data is permanently removed from our
        systems:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong> — your name, email address, and profile details</li>
        <li><strong>Project data</strong> — all projects you created, including budgets, cost codes, and vendor information</li>
        <li><strong>Expense records</strong> — every expense entry, approval, and financial record associated with your account</li>
        <li><strong>Receipt images</strong> — all uploaded receipt photos and scanned documents</li>
        <li><strong>Team memberships</strong> — your membership in any project teams (other team members' data is not affected)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Important Information</h2>
      <p>
        Account deletion is <strong>permanent and cannot be undone</strong>. Once your
        account is deleted, your data cannot be recovered. If you have an active
        subscription, please cancel it through your app store (Apple App Store or Google
        Play Store) before deleting your account to avoid further charges.
      </p>

      <h2>Need Help?</h2>
      <p>
        If you are unable to access the app or need assistance deleting your account,
        please contact us at
        <a href="mailto:support@getfierro.com">support@getfierro.com</a> and we will
        process your request.
      </p>
      <p>
        For information about how we handle your data, please review our
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
